(279, 1, '2014-07-12 07:24:22', '2014-07-12 07:24:22', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12">\r\n\r\nNightForce G7 Scopes\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith tactical tasks in mind, these manufactured by Nightforce Optics rifle scopes bring some more custom features which any user – hunter, long range bench rest shooter or military sniper can really enjoy.\r\n\r\nG7 scopes come with famous G7 ballistic compensation technology and fully customized ballistic match turret adjustment knob. Scope reticle give shooter opportunity make fast, simple and precise ballistic compensation while shooting, depending on used ammo and weather state.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBR II Rangefinder\r\n\r\nWith Nightforce Optics strict control and tests system, G7 rifle scope equipped with cemented lens assembly, meet every important standard which mean solid and rugged rifle scope with excellent repeatability shoot after shoot. For low light performance The G7 BR2 (Ballistic Rangefinder 2000) rangefinder has achieved the most significant milestone in laser rangefinder technology since their introduction to the hunting industry. The BR2 model is the first rangefinder to feature a real time ballistic calculation that accepts your specific bullet Ballistic Coefficient and Muzzle Velocity as inputs to build a custom ballistic profile, and then calculate a real time ballistic solution.\r\n\r\nThe impressive ranging capability comes from Laser Technologies Inc, one of the world’s premier professional measurement companies. New developments in sensor technology along with dozens of other patented technologies give the G7 BR2 eye safe ranging capabilities beyond 2000 yards.\r\n\r\nBy utilizing the G7 ballistic engine, the G7 BR2 is able to utilize measurements of line of sight range, incline angle, and air density to make a complete ballistic calculation of the Shoot To range for your custom bullet drop compensating reticle or turret. “Just range it and dial it” has never been so simple or precise.\r\n\r\nscope has high quality lens system, matched and tuned by hands of experienced engineer to provide the highest optical performance ever possible.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'NIGHTFORCE G7 SCOPES/RANGEFINDERS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '264-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-12 07:24:22', '2014-07-12 07:24:22', '', 264, 'http://endtoenddesigns.com/huntthedistance/264-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(280, 1, '2014-07-12 07:29:56', '2014-07-12 07:29:56', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12">\r\n\r\nHuskemaw\r\n\r\nWith technical <a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_007.htm">advancements</a> like True BC, the Rapid Field Ballistic Compensator and the <a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_007.htm">simple</a> yet powerful Hunt Smart range finding and windage compensating reticle. The 30mm main tube, 50mm objective lens, and side focus parallax correction dial make the Huskemaw LR scopes an outstanding choice for both varmint hunters and <a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_007.htm">target</a> shooters. It also includes <a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_007.htm">special</a> features for the <a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_007.htm">big game hunter</a>. Ballistic compensation and parallax adjustments are easily made without breaking shooting position, and the 42mm or 50mm objective lens'' create a bright, clear image for high magnification and low light use.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Features</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Windage Compensation Technology</li>\r\n	<li>True BC Drop Compensation</li>\r\n	<li>Hunt Smart Reticle</li>\r\n	<li>30mm Maintube</li>\r\n	<li>Fast Focus Eyepiece</li>\r\n	<li>Full <a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_007.htm">Lifetime Guarantee</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'HUSKEMAW SCOPES', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '262-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-12 07:29:56', '2014-07-12 07:29:56', '', 262, 'http://endtoenddesigns.com/huntthedistance/262-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(281, 1, '2014-07-15 01:07:36', '2014-07-15 01:07:36', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12">\r\n\r\n<strong>Custom Systems</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Our custom rifles or packages  are assembled with all the components that we feel hold the best tolerances for repeatability. Because nothing is more important than being able to repeat something over and over. With repeatability comes performance, and with performance and repeatability comes precision. </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            We use custom actions, custom barrels, recoil lugs,  stocks and muzzle brakes  (are standard but if chosen would not be put on your rifle). We feel through this process can we only hold the tightest of tolerances, to get consistent repeatability. We are not trying to assemble as many rifles as we can and just throw them out the door. Our custom rifles are not done until it has been shot to prove what it is capable of. Our custom rifles have 1/2" at 100 yard guarantee. </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            In our custom rifles we use a lot of stiller actions, along with some others if Stiller''s time frame is too far out. We have used just about every manufactures barrels, and have not encountered any that stood out above another to make a extremely accurate hunting rifle. We have a couple companies that do special barrel fluting to make your custom even more custom and stand out above anything else you have seen. </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            Rifle stocks.  We have been using HS Precision, Grey bull and McMillan.  As the long range shooting has developed so has the design of the </strong><a href="http://www.huntthedistance.com/hunt_the_distance_new_101_012.htm"><strong>rifle stock</strong></a><strong>. The main long range stock designs have a vertical grip. The vertical grip has a much more forgiving and comfortable grip. Which in return helps be more consistent and forgiving. I really like the McMillan stock like the A-3 or A-5 adjustable cheek piece. The cheek piece on these stocks is much easier to adjust and really seem not to move even if you apply a lot of cheek weld. </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Please contact Jason at 406-491-6109 or email info@huntthedistance.com, for more information on our custom systems.</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'CUSTOM SYSTEMS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '260-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-15 01:07:36', '2014-07-15 01:07:36', '', 260, 'http://endtoenddesigns.com/huntthedistance/260-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
