(309, 1, '2014-07-17 07:43:48', '2014-07-17 07:43:48', '<div class="row">\n<div class="col-lg-12">\n\n<h1>Custom Systems</h1>\n\n<p style="font-size:18px;">Our custom rifles or packages  are assembled with all the components that we feel hold the best tolerances for repeatability. Because nothing is more important than being able to repeat something over and over. With repeatability comes performance, and with performance and repeatability comes precision.</p>\n\n<p style="font-size:18px;">We use custom actions, custom barrels, recoil lugs,  stocks and muzzle brakes  (are standard but if chosen would not be put on your rifle). We feel through this process can we only hold the tightest of tolerances, to get consistent repeatability. We are not trying to assemble as many rifles as we can and just throw them out the door. Our custom rifles are not done until it has been shot to prove what it is capable of. Our custom rifles have 1/2" at 100 yard guarantee. </p>\n\n<p style="font-size:18px;">In our custom rifles we use a lot of stiller actions, along with some others if Stiller''s time frame is too far out. We have used just about every manufactures barrels, and have not encountered any that stood out above another to make a extremely accurate hunting rifle. We have a couple companies that do special barrel fluting to make your custom even more custom and stand out above anything else you have seen. </p>\n\n<p style="font-size:18px;">Rifle stocks.  We have been using HS Precision, Grey bull and McMillan.  As the long range shooting has developed so has the design of the </p><a href="custom-systems"><p style="font-size:18px;">rifle stock</strong></a><strong>. The main long range stock designs have a vertical grip. The vertical grip has a much more forgiving and comfortable grip. Which in return helps be more consistent and forgiving. I really like the McMillan stock like the A-3 or A-5 adjustable cheek piece. The cheek piece on these stocks is much easier to adjust and really seem not to move even if you apply a lot of cheek weld. </strong>\n\n<p style="font-size:18px;">Please contact Jason at 406-491-6109 or email info@huntthedistance.com, for more information on our custom systems.</strong>\n\n</div>\n</div>', 'CUSTOM SYSTEMS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '260-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-07-17 07:43:48', '2014-07-17 07:43:48', '', 260, 'http://endtoenddesigns.com/huntthedistance/260-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
